Jurgen Klopp has released Liverpool’s squad for the Champions League knockout stage against Atletico Madrid. The German, however, made one notable change. He has added his £7.25m January signing, Takumi Minamino to the squad that will see off the remainder of the competition. Minamino took the place of Sepp van den Berg, in the squad. The Reds will face LaLiga giants, Atletico Madrid in the last 16, the first leg of which takes place in Spain on February 18 with the Anfield return three weeks later on March 11. Liverpool’s full squad include, Goalkeepers: Alisson Becker, Adrian, Andy Lonergan, Caoimhin Kelleher Defenders: Virgil van Dijk, Dejan Lovren, Joe Gomez, Andy Robertson, Joel Matip, Adam Lewis, Trent Alexander-Arnold, Neco Williams, Yasser Larouci Midfielders: Fabinho, Georginio Wijnaldum, James Milner, Naby Keita, Jordan Henderson, Alex Oxlade-Chamberlain, Adam Lallana, Xherdan Shaqiri, Curtis Jones, Harvey Elliott Forwards: Roberto Firmino, Sadio Mane, Mohamed Salah, Takumi Minamino, Divock Origi